Method Detail

visit

boolean visit(Quadtree.Node<T> node,
              double x1,
              double y1,
              double x2,
              double y2)
Called for each node of the quadtree.

When true is returned for a node, then the children of that node are not visited.

Parameters:
node - the visited node
x1 - the top left x coordinate
y1 - the top left y coordinate
x2 - the bottom right x coordinate
y2 - the bottom right y coordinate
Returns:
false if children should be visited, true otherwise
